 {"id":"bd-39t","title":"Implement include_tags/exclude_tags filtering","description":"# Implement include_tags/exclude_tags Filtering

## Background
Python FastMCP supports filtering components by tags during listing operations. This enables clients to request only relevant tools/resources/prompts based on their needs, and servers to control visibility of components.

## Requirements

### ListToolsRequest Extension
```rust
/// Extended list request with tag filtering
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct ListToolsRequest {
    /// Only include components with ALL of these tags
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    pub include_tags: Option<Vec<String>>,

    /// Exclude components with ANY of these tags
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    pub exclude_tags: Option<Vec<String>>,
}
```

### Server-Side Filtering
```rust
impl Router {
    pub fn list_tools_filtered(
        &self,
        include_tags: Option<&[String]>,
        exclude_tags: Option<&[String]>,
    ) -> Vec<Tool> {
        self.tools.values()
            .filter(|tool| {
                // Include filter: tool must have ALL include tags
                if let Some(include) = include_tags {
                    if !include.iter().all(|tag| tool.tags().contains(tag)) {
                        return false;
                    }
                }

                // Exclude filter: tool must NOT have ANY exclude tags
                if let Some(exclude) = exclude_tags {
                    if exclude.iter().any(|tag| tool.tags().contains(tag)) {
                        return false;
                    }
                }

                true
            })
            .map(|h| h.to_tool())
            .collect()
    }
}
```

### Filter Semantics
- `include_tags`: AND logic - component must have ALL specified tags
- `exclude_tags`: OR logic - component excluded if it has ANY specified tag
- Both can be combined: include AND exclude filters apply together
- Case-insensitive matching (normalize to lowercase)
- Empty array = no filter (different from None)

## Files to Modify
